III. A Wilful Lyar.
The Content. Apoſtate, &c. p. 3. F. Bugg and his Company being got to the Meeting before G. W. and into the Gallery where our Miniſtring Friends uſed to be, &c. In ſhort 'tis falſe, and that to G. Whitehead's Knowledge too;
for there was not a Man of my Company in the Gallery with me, but S. Cater; and this he wilfully and maliciouſly ſent abroad, to render me a turbulent Diſturber; which is fully proved in New Rome unm. &c. p. 50, 51.
